%h4#attendees <small>3.1</small> Get attendee list
.meta
  .method GET
  .url /event/attendees[/:state].json

.description
  Using this endpoint you can get the list of attendees along with it's tickets

  %h5 Available parameters
  %table.table.table-striped.well
    %col{width: '30%'}
    %col{width: '70%'}
    %thead
      %tr
        %th Parameter
        %th Description
    %tbody
      %tr
        %td state (optional)
        %td
          To filter the list by the attendee state.
          The available states are:
          %ul
            %li
              %strong checked
              Filter only attendees with checked tickets
            %li
              %strong unchecked
              Filter only attendees with unchecked tickets
      %tr
        %td ticket_id (optional)
        %td To filter the attendees with tickets for a given ticket_id
      %tr
        %td since (optional)
        %td
          An ISO8601 encoded date to filter attendees updated since the given
          date.

  .example
    = code(line_numbers: false) do
      :plain
        curl -i -H 'Authorization: event TOKEN' \
          https://api.welcu.com/v1/event/attendees/checked.json

